{{Infobox film | name = Garbage Warrior | image = Garbage warrior movie poster.jpg | caption = Michael Reynolds standing on a Earthship construction area in Taos, New Mexico | director = [[Oliver Hodge]] | producer = [[Rachel Wexler]] | starring = [[Mike Reynolds (architect)|Mike Reynolds]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2007|04||Hotdocs Film Festival}} | runtime = | country = United States | language = English | budget =$1.5 million | gross = }} '''''Garbage Warrior''''' is a 2007 film about architect [[Mike Reynolds (architect)|Mike Reynolds]], inventor of the [[Earthship]] style of building, directed by [[Oliver Hodge]]. It follows Reynolds and how he developed the [[Earthship]] style of building and his struggle with the laws of [[Taos, New Mexico]], the location of his experimental Earthship community, in order to be allowed to build homes that do not match the structures of local [[building codes]]. The film concludes with a postscript showing Reynolds and his team of builders travelling to the [[Andaman Islands]] in the aftermath of the [[Boxing Day tsunami]] to assist the locals with disaster recovery and teaching them how to construct extremely low-cost earthships.
